street_address: 4972 Campanile Drive, San Diego, CA, United States
referred: This report has been referred to appropriate department or agency at MGray@sandiego.gov
public_description: SDSU's address is on this same street (Campanile Dr), but after crossing an intersection, it becomes residential, housing mostly students and some families. There are 3 streetlights total. One is completely covered by trees, and the others omit a dull glow. Cars line the sides of the street 24/7, as well as large bushes and trees, meaning that anyone who walks at night is hidden. On 9/31 at 10:00pm, I was walking home when a man attacked me on the sidewalk in front of my home and strangled me in a bush for a minute. I nearly lost consciousness before something startled him enough to run away. He was going to rape or kill me. There was no way anyone could see me, and my attacker planned that spot because of that. A few weeks prior, two students were robbed at gunpoint at night just a few houses up the street. The lack of lighting provides a perfect environment for a criminal to act, and college students are a huge target as it is. Lighting is absolutely necessary for our safety. This is dangerous.
